## Interaction Contract

- Clicking while `disabled` or while a copy operation is already running is ignored.
- `copy` is emitted only after clipboard write succeeds.
- `error` is emitted with the thrown error when both clipboard strategies fail.
- `copiedLabel` is shown for `timeout` milliseconds after success, then the button returns to `copyLabel`.
- The default slot receives `{ copied, copying }` when the host needs custom content.

## API

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `text` | `string` | `''` | Text written to the clipboard. |
| `copyLabel` | `string` | `'Copy'` | Idle label and aria-label. |
| `copiedLabel` | `string` | `'Copied'` | Success label and aria-label. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables the button and prevents copy. |
| `timeout` | `number` | `1400` | Milliseconds before copied state resets. |
| `size` | `'sm' \| 'md'` | `'sm'` | Button density. |

### Events

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| `copy` | `(text: string)` | Emitted after successful clipboard write. |
| `error` | `(error: unknown)` | Emitted when clipboard write fails. |

### Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `default` | `{ copied, copying }` | Custom button label/content. |

## Best Practices

- Use short, explicit `copyLabel` text that names the target, such as “Copy token” or “Copy command”.
- Handle `error` when the copied value is critical; browsers can reject clipboard writes outside trusted gestures.
- Do not put secrets in ordinary docs examples or analytics when copy events fire.
- Keep the copied text in host state so it is easy to audit and test.

